I have created an 
implementation plan
 for Red Fortress.

Building this multiplayer board game is fully possible using a modern TypeScript stack. Before we begin, please check the plan and review the following open questions:

Card Draw Details: When a player collects money, do they draw a random card from the face-down deck, or is there a face-up "money market" of cards they can choose from?

Rearrange Tile Rules: When a player chooses to rearrange a tile, can they move any tile from their board back to their reserve, or swap it with another, as long as connectivity to the Fountain is maintained?

Tile Reserve: Do players have a "Reserve" space where they can store purchased tiles before placing them on their board?

Tile Walls & Alignments: In Alhambra, building tiles have walls on certain sides. Must we implement these wall alignment constraints, or is basic edge-adjacency enough?

